{
  "texts": [
    "Our findings indicate that moderate pruning does not significantly impact language modeling performance on WikiText.",
    "However, this observation may not necessarily extrapolate to artificial constructs such as jailbreak templates.",
    "Indeed, it might even be preferable to have language models that do not overfit to such out-of-distribution prompts.",
    "We approach this by investigating the perplexity assigned by both base and sparse models, to both the original malicious tasks and the prompts constructed using jailbreak templates.",
    "Note that model responses are not included in the following perplexity calculations."
  ]
}